    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "summary": "This prophetic tradition conveys that death itself serves as an expiation (kaffara) for the sins of believers. In Islamic theology, this hadith provides comfort to the faithful by affirming that the experience of death purifies the believer from accumulated sins. The hadith was transmitted through Imam Ja'far al-Sadiq from the Prophet Muhammad himself.",
